The electronic transport coefficients were obtained by solving the semiclassical Boltzmann transport equation (BTE) under the constant relaxation time approximation (CRTA), as implemented in BoltzTraP code38. The Boltzmann equation describes the change of carrier distribution function induced by external fields, lattice phonon scattering, or different kinds of defect scattering39. Due to the complexity of various carrier scattering mechanisms, it is almost impossible to obtain an exact solution of the Boltzmann equation. For simplicity, the relaxation time approximation is used. The Boltzmann method is widely used for the evaluation of transport properties of 2D materials and provides a good agreement with the experimental measurements2. In this method, the electronic band structure ε\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
